      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson introduces how artificial intelligence is being used to support building materials selection, with a focus on the key risks that professionals need to understand. You will explore how AI tools can help assess the durability of materials, check compliance with building regulations, and evaluate environmental suitability for different project contexts. We will also look at where AI can fall short, including the limitations of data quality, the risk of over-reliance on automated recommendations, and the importance of professional judgement. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of how to use AI responsibly as part of your materials selection process. No prior experience with AI is required, and all concepts are explained in plain, practical terms.",
